      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>On reaction with acid, 4-pyrone is protonated on the carbonyl-group oxygen to give a stable cationic product. Using resonance structures and the Hückel 4<i>n</i> + 2 rule, explain why the protonated product is so stable.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBajRWIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--2705b6d53d730970257a576d2cc3d2903853758d/OChem_15_EC_017.jpg\" alt=\"4-Pyrone, when treated wuth acid is protonated at the carbonyl group, the oxygen of which now carries a positive charge.\">",
